The paper discusses modifications to the definition of Shannon entropy, which is a concept commonly used in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with probability laws and their inconsistencies, which are relevant to the subfield of computer science concerned with algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The proposed modifications to entropy could have implications for machine learning and data analysis, which fall under the categories of cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.LG (machine learning). Finally, the paper's discussion of entropy and its properties could be relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC).
